\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid2641324 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 22 Exley Road, Ingrow, Keighley, Yorkshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And you're married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I hope so, yes, (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, we've been married 40 year, so that's ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 1930?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Roughly, yes. Aye, that's it, it would be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And the year when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And the place where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oakworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How long did you live at the house in Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I were 4 when I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Ingrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And when you moved to Ingrow did you stay in one house in Ingrow for any length of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes? Quite some time up to ... no ... until we've been married, but we moved only a few doors away that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I see, yes, I see. Have you any idea why it was that you moved from Oakworth to Ingrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, only that ... No, I wouldn't think so, only that the parent's work were in Keighley, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I see. You think they would move to be nearer to the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 To the job, that's it. I would think that was the only thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 One brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was he older or younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Two years older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How old was your father when you were born, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 He died at 59 through War complications, aggravated with gas burns on t'chest he took pneumonia
, and my son is 36 ... 34 years since. It's 36 years since he died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 He died 34 years ago and he was 59 then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. He died with pneumonia, complications of gas burns on chest through 1914 war, that were in his Certificate, you see. Me mother liv
ed 10 year afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was she about the same age as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 She were the same age, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 He was born in Keighley, but they were originally Kendal people, me grandparents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You say he worked for the Gas Board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Gas Board, yes, under the old Corporation then. Not the North Eastern Gas Board, the old corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I should think just a corporation gas worker's labourer. They renovated ... when the dev
ices came in t'gas room they had 'em cleaned and renovated them up, you know. Actually, he were an outdoor worker to start with, mains and that sort of thing. And owing to being wounded during the '14 - '18 War he went inside on their behalf, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he have any other job before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, I would think that was his job all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you know if he ever did any casual or part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, he didn't believe in it. He didn't believe in it. He were a working man and he didn't
 believe in doing anything ... interfere with anybody else with regards occupation. And he wouldn't even do his own decorating and paper - hanging, that sort of thing that they do today. I'd be surprised if people in ... living round here that'll do it th
e
mselves rather than pay for somebody else that makes a living, which he disagreed with, and I think I follow in his footsteps because I've paid for all mine all the years. I've never used a paint brush or anything ... interfered with any other trade, or i
ndustry, you see. On principle, not because ... financially, but just on principle. And we've got through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No, but of course in those days ... of course, I've heard him talk about being laid
 off for 14 weeks in winter with a hard frost on t'building trade. You see, he was more or less an outdoor worker and in those days there were no compensation. Today I understand that the building trades and outdoor workers is at least 52% standing rate w
h
ether they work a week or not. That's guaranteed. But previous, in these days ... the old days, if there was 14 weeks frost as we're talking about - and I heard him talk about it - they were laid off and there were no dole, there were no compensation, and
 there were no pay, and they had to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember any of these.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
I don't justly remember it, but it were within my time. Must have been, you see. Fourteen weeks, one bit that he talked about, probably be the longest they did, through fros
t and hard weather. They couldn't get down to it. But the materials that they used in them days according to the material that they're using today ... plasters and such like, building materials ... they couldn't use them in the old days. Now they've diffe
rent materials, now, in t'building trades, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Your father wasn't actually occupied in the building trade, though, was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I would think as a younger man, yes, and then he went on to the Corporation. Yes. Which you can call outdoor working,
 laying mains for the Corporation until he was wounded, and then he went inside, you see, he couldn't do this outdoor work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You think he started off in the building trade, do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, you're going back a long way. I would think he were a mould
er to start with, but they didn't do long at moulding. Several relatives of his age, they were all moulders, but they finished at a very early age. They didn't ... And a lot of them died at an early age, did moulders, at that period. I would think, what I
 remember about 'em, an average of 60 years were a length of life at that time for moulders. I don't know what it is today, mind you. But it seemed to take so much out of them that they had such an early death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You say your mother was about the same age as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Same age, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, she were born locally. I would think Oakworth, I don't know. But they came from Norfolk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Her family. My great-uncles and -aunts came from Norfolk and there were 18 of them. Eighteen of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Your mother was one of the 18?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, me mother was one of the nieces. But her family came from Norfolk, her parents and uncles and aunts came from Norfolk. A family of 18 they were. And why they came he
re, they came to work in the mills, an industry of Yorkshire, you see. That were the idea. They originally came ... The great-grand parents were estate people, you know, worked on estates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Ye
s, she worked. And she worked ... oh, 'till after the 1914 War which I told you this morning, she had to do because the Army pay in them days weren't too much. And she worked, mainly, at Robert Clough's again, piece mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that what she was doing all the time, before she was married and after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I would say so, yes. To my knowledge, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was she working full time during the War when your father was away?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 With the exception that they let her out that hour off some part of t'd
ay to let her get home to us. Perhaps that were half an hour later and her come home half an hour early. But not always so, they didn't always allow that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she finish working then, when your father ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 She were finished after the 1914 War, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Who looked after the children while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
We went to school and came home with door locked. Well, he'd to get in ourselves, like. And unfortunately, those days you came home from school wintertime without fire, you know. A
nd when they were working, my father were in France, me mother were working and you came home without fire and you just did what you could 'till they came home from work half past 5 at night. From 4 o'clock school. I mean, we'd plenty neighbours and frien
d
s that were good enough to let us spend a bit of time with them. I never remember a time when I were fast for ... left actually on t'street. We could either go into t'neighbours or go into our own home. And we were reasonably decent for a working-class fa
m
ily, at that. Respectable. In these days we were quite a respectable family, even in them conditions. Thought a lot about ... Me father went to a congregational church and took an active part there, and me mother did. Acted in all t'plays and all that sor
t of thing, you know, led an active life and public life and she were a very good elocutionist, was me mother. She could get up and talk ... elocution for the hour. She could, she were jolly good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Had she been trained?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The house that you lived at - we'll take the one at Ingrow that you moved to when you were 4.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Which we was in the biggest part of the time up to me getting married. It were only a year to two before we ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you tell me how many rooms there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Yes. It was on a main road, a row of cottages on a main road, with one livingroom, one kitchen and two bedrooms, covered by stone floors. Solid flagstone floors. Sanitary arrangements was outside, and part of this property, if we dare talk this, the sewe
rs were taken away by the Corporation sewage people once a week in empty tubs, before the w.c.'s came into operation, you see. And it were mainly done between 10 o'clock at night and 2 o'clock in t'morning. If you got to bed late you could hear them tramp
i
ng on ... the horse vehicle collecting and emptying these tubs and that's how the sewage was taken away. And I would think in Ingrow today there's some still left, the odd ones, in them conditions. And we weren't electric, then, it were gas, you know, and
 
not gas in all places. Probably your front bedroom might have had gas, but you'd a candle for your back bedroom. I remember that quite well, anyway. And stone sinks, solid stone sinks in your kitchen. And an iron fireplace which heated ... the only motive
 of heating your water and the only means of cooking. An oven at one side and a boiler at the other and then you put your pans on t'open fire to cook with. And that were all before 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did anybody else live in the house besides your parents and you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, just we ... me father and we two.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother ever have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No. She managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Even when she was going out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Even when she was going out to work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The washing was done at home by the old wringing machine and the old peg-it-up system. No vacuums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother or father make or mend any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No, they weren't gifted in that sense. Fortunately they are tod
ay, both my daughter-in-law ... and that generation, they are. They make their own clothes. But in those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 So your clothes would all be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Clothes was all bought, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, they were always bought
 in Keighley, because Ingrow hadn't a clothing stores at all, and it hasn't today. So we had to go to Keighley for our clothes which is a mile distance, isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go to any particular shop, or did you shop around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, if it isn't too p
ersonal, that, and I don't mind saying it, a lot of people in those days - and probably we were on the fringe of it - they went with a coupon from an agent and got them on so much a week, a little bit. They did, honestly. And so they were obliged to go to
 these stores where they carried that system, but not always so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You think that that happened with some of your things, do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I think yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would the clothes always be new clothes that were bought for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 New clothes, oh, yes, d
efinitely. Definitely. Not too much of that system, but it was done. I mean, it's no disgrace because ... I mean, it was done all over. It is today, but I've never done it in my time. I said that would stop after I were married. I said nobody would come t
o our house. I said nobody would come collecting rents nor nothing and I managed to save and buy me own from the beginning. Through mortgages, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a child how often would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, it were systematic with us. It were Wh
itsuntide for a walking day and you guaranteed, if there were any new clothes it were for Whitsuntide, Sunday School walk. And they lasted more or less for 12 months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we'd shoes for Sunday, but we'd clogs for 6 days a week. Clogs. And if you've lived in Lancashire you'll know what they are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father do any mending of your clogs, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no. But you see, as I said, he were away 4 year of my schooling. I never remember him putting a clog iron on. No, m
e mother went out to work to compensate for what we lost through the 1914 War, and did it through work, and she became a boss mender, which was a slight achievement, to become a boss mender and have a certain amount of young girls and women under her; to 
be head mender, sort of style, you see. As regards textiles, I mean. I don't mean regards to modern science.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Your clogs, and so on, would they be bought in Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, yes. Bought in Keighley and made in Keighley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How often would you have new clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, that dependedon use, didn't it? Say we'd have new clogs at least once a year, or more. 'Cos you used to kick 'em to bits, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And then you'd be growing, as well, wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And growing, yes. And there were a 
system in them days, if it's sense to this sort of thing, that when you went away to school you clamp your legs ... you clamp your feet, irons on your clogs and cause them to cause sparks. Well, they last less ... they didn't last as long, did they?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father ever help your mother with any of the jobs in the house? You know, cleaning, cooking or washing up, anything like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I don't really think so, no. Not because he were biased in doing it but I don't think there were any need for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would he make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, he'd light the fire and things all men should do, but as regards to washing, baking and mending, nothing like that, no. Nor decorating, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And he wasn't a do-it-yourself man at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. On principle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he do anything for you as children? Like dressing, or undressing, or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, I never remember him doing, and I never remember doing any with my family. But my son's done a lot for his, because they seem to do a lot more today than what they did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would he look after you while your mother went out, or would he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 He'd do both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he read to you or tell you stories, as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I never remember my father doing it. Of course, this 4 years seemed to be a long while, the '14 War, but my mother would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any jobs to do in the house to help your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, only fetching coal and finding firewood, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about while your father was away, did you have any jobs assigned to you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, we were so young, you see, she were glad that we were healthy and playing out and she could get on. We'd no need to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And it was true of your brother, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, yes. I'd healthy parents, you see, they didn't need it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your brother do anything to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, funny thing about it, we were quite a happy family, but we both
 found our own mates, so we had very little contact between one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, of course, under old-fashioned methods that there were in them days, just gaslight, an
d no televisions and wirelesses, you did go to bed early in these days, didn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But did you have to? Was there a stipulated time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Only the school had a card up, advising you to go to bed at 8 o'clock at night, you see, and we more or less st
uck to us, because us parents had to get up to work the next morning, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was it your mother who put you to bed as a child? Or did your father do, sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I can't speak, only for the time as we was capable of going to bed ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You don't remember before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, I don't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 About how old do you think you'd be when you were putting yourselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, 6 and 7.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And did you share the bedroom or the bed with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Shared it, yes. Yes, we'd only 2 bedrooms and we'd to share the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You didn't have a bathroom, did you? You had the tin bath arrangement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The tin bath brought up weekly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was this in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, it wasn't because there were no heatings in
 kitchens in those days, and there isn't in a big percentage of that type of house today which is in existence. So it was to bring on to the hearthrug by the fire in the only livingroom we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have clean clothes to put on related to having had your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, yes. Oh, yes, we were never in want of anything like that, oh, no. Oh, no. We were never in want of anything like that, we'd always a change of clothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have your meals in the livingroom or in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The kitchens weren't big enough. We'd to have them in t'livingroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you ever eat anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 In our own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, mainly in the house, in the livingroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Your mother cooked on this range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was there any gas ring or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
The gas rings came between 1910 and '20, somewhere. Somewhere in that period, the gas rings. And then the gas ovens started to come through, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother have one in the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 A gas oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Or a gas ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, not probably as early as some people, but we weren't too far behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But in your schooldays she didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, in the early schooldays she hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you tell me something about the meals: the times that you had meals and the sort of food that you had to eat, and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Between 8 and 9 o'clock in the morning we'd have our breakfast, which was very plain, very plain; bread and cheese, and jam, and that kind of thing. You know, there weren't a lot of sweet things 
in them days. They weren't to be bought, and they couldn't afford them if they were to be bought. I would think we got a share of fruit, and that kind of thing. And then dinnertimes, they'd some system than for a lot of years when there were women in t'di
s
trict, if Mother made a pie and put a crust on it the night before, they would cook it for them and charge so much for cooking. So you got a meat and potato pie once a week. Another person would probably make such things as savoury ducks, that were well k
n
own. That would be another meal. And, of course, she would call at local butcher's coming from her work and cook such things as sausage, that were easy to cook, when she hadn't time to make a full meal herself but she could make a cooked meal with things 
like ... sort of half cooked, you know what I mean. And teatimes, again, well, it would be what everybody had. Of course, in the old-fashioned days they used to get a lot of cockles and mussels and kippers, and that kind of thing, and cook 'em themselves.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
This system of someone doing the pie, and so on, did your mother make use of that while she was working? Or did she make use of that all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, it would be once a week, at least, with this pie day, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But all the time? Not just while she was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 While she were at home she would make a pie herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 This is what I meant, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But when she was at work there were these neighbours who were trying to get a copper or two for themselves, were prepared to cook thi
s pie. Of it you took your piedish empty they'd make a pie for you for so much. And if they went out ... to take her washing in those days you could get it done for a shilling or half a crown. A whole week's wash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But your mother never did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 She washed, herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Presumably you would have something to drink at the mealtimes, as well, wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Mainly tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 For breakfast, dinner and tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 For breakfast, dinner and tea. Mainly tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have anything before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Only that. There was no such things as minerals bought in those days, to any extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You didn't have a proper supper at bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about Sundays? Did you have anything different then, or on any other special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
All I can think of on Sunday, she did make a meal at Sunday dinnertime which was exceptional, owing to her going to work, you see. And she would make a good meal, then, of beef, Yorkshire pudding, potatoes and vegetables. A good hot meal. N
owadays they have them more or less every meal, but .... There was no school meals in those days to be got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you all go home for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father go home when he was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no, he stayed to eat at hi
s work. And she had just an hour to come home and get back, and provide us with a dinner and get back to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she bake her own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. Yes, she did, baked her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about making jam and bottling fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Occas
ionally, yes, they'd do that, in seasons, of course. She would do that. And occasionally, at this period she would get down and make a baking bowlful of nettle beer and bottle that. Well, that were our change for what they have for meals today, we had ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she make pickles or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, occasionally. We'd a garden and we'd grow shallots and she'd pickle them, you know, but no wine. Never bothered with wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about medicines, did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did they grow their own vegetables and fruit, apart from the shallots that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, we grew a lot because in the 1914 War I dug a ... with my brother-in-law, as boys, we dug our first allotment up and so we always ... and we have today, always had our own allotment and garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you grow enough to keep yourselves going, or did you have to buy some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, we'd to buy beside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were vegetables or fruit ever bought in tins, or dried, or was it always fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not in those days. It was all fresh. I think there's more today ... a lot more today than what there were then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no, you could buy plenty of fresh meat and it were reasonable in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 About how often would you have fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, if you counted putting it into pies, and beefsteak puddings and roast beefs, method, we'd have it more or less every day. Oh, yes, we weren't too badly done with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents keep any livestock for the family - hens, pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, they never did, but I've done in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you know whether there was any poaching done in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, there was, but not amongst our family. But there was poachers in the area, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you ever acquire any of the poached ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, on principle again, my father wouldn't accepted any if he'd known it to have been stolen. As a working man and a common labourer he'd a terrible high principle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember ever seeing your mother go short of a favourite dish, or food generally, so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, yes, there were times when we would've liked to have a thing, but we didn't get 'em, she couldn't get 'em. She'd to make do and mend, so to speak. Both for food and clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But did she actually - do you remember whether she actually went short herself so that you could have ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, she never did that. No, she'd never ... no need to go to that extent, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father have more to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, he weren't exceptional, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you allowed to talk during the meal as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, slightly, but if there were any foolishness we were sent into t'corner for a minute or two to be quiet from the table. As children you would probably hear something and laugh about it and it
 would ... I remember being put in t'corner, stand there 'till you'd quieten off. But not brutally, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything that was prepared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I would thi
nk cooking in those days, you hadn't a choice, it were one thing. It were either the boiled pudding, or the potato pie, or this one weekend with beefsteak and vegetables, and then, probably a lighter dinner, sausage and mash, those sort of meals. And you 
got plenty of that one thing, but you hadn't a variety.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was your parents' attitude if you left anything uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, they weren't abrupt with us at all. No, they were very moderate, if you didn't feel to want it it were all right. But my p
arents enjoyed good health, up to War wounds, and I've enjoyed good health through it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
If there was something on the table that you wanted, like the salt for instance, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, we'd ask it to be passed to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Could you ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, yes, yes, yes. And there was that about it, because it was one dish and plenty of it, but at a moderate price. You know, it were wholesome food, but cheap food - potatoes and meat and crust with gravy (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way? And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well I can't say that ever that were a question. We seemed to learn them things as time w
ent on and on our own. Different to my grandchildren because they are taught that way, and been taught that way because they've enjoyed more amenities than ever we've known and they've enjoyed hotel life which is extent to what we ever enjoyed, you see, a
nd so they've been obliged to learn their children. But I think that's one of the advancements as regards table life that youngsters has today that we hadn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Could you bring toys or a book to the table of a mealtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about leaving the table, when could you leave? Did you have to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 There were no set method at all, get up and leave it if we felt like it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you all sit at the table for your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When we was at home together, but there weren't many meals that me father were sat with us apart from weekends, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was it your mother who served up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, Mother served table, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she have any special order of serving you in, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you tell me something about the sort of person your mother was. Was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Me mother was quite pleasant, good looking, very smart, and she'd no education but self-educated and she were v
ery good. As I said, she could stand up and give elocution for an hour at a time, or get on to a public platform and read a lesson at school or anything like that, and be acknowledged tremendously for it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel about your relationship with her as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Very good. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you feel you could confide in her if you had any worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Always. Always. And we had to do owing to that four years co's nobody else ... And she never left us for anything. She never went anywh
ere without we were with her, apart from going to work. 'Cos, there were picture houses, you know, in them days and we'd go to local pictures when piano were playing instead of a orchestra and it were the old silent pictures, and we'd all go together, com
e back with an armful of fish and chips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother show her affection for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, yes, as much as she'd time for. As much as she'd time for, definitely, yes. Definitely. What time and privilege she had, she gave it to us. Without a doubt. 
But when a woman went out to work 8 hours a day and Father soldiered in France there weren't a lot of time to be spent with you, was there? There wasn't. Not when she had her own housework to do and cooking and cleaning and mending and shopping. As I tell
 
you, we were healthy children and we found us our own friends and played out. And we'd a village community, there weren't nothing to be frightened of those days, there were no traffic on roads, you could play football on roads in them days, on what were c
alled the main roads then, like Ingrow Lann i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2167424\charrsid2688408 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
 today. You could play football and no interference, there were no cars. They can't do it today. That's what this youth today is short of. Everywhere they put their feet they're trespassing, today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I know your father was away all this time, but was he easy to talk to and could you confide in him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 ... in the time that he was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, yes, yes. Quite happy family, there were no ... nothing interfered with family li
fe at all. We'd quite a clean record in all respects.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Just as we'd expect them to be to us. Just like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brother in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, as I say, we've always belonged to the same congregational church, four generations of us, and we've always been respected through it, and we've tried to live as near to it as we could and it's always been so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents say that you should hit back, or not, if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, on the contrary. Me father ... One particular time one of us complained about being hit by the schoolteacher and he went to the school, he said 'hit them again if they needed it' (laughter) That 
was funny you should mention that, but it was, though. But that weren't the continuation of things, but it happened once and that were the motive, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, like any w
orking class people they hoped that we'd turn out everything to best of his ability without wanting to ... expecting too much. But as I say, we hadn't the education that there is today we didn't go along ... we didn't ... we had four or 5 years less at sc
hool than they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did they bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, I don't think they really did. I don't think they were really concerned about things like that, as long as you were healthy, and they saw that we got plenty of food, we were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, as I say, we belonged to the congregational church, I never knew any swearing at home. I never heard a word at home all the time I were a child. Not from the parents or from us. You do today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When the grownups were talking could the children join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We was taught not to interfere and we was taught to talk if we were asked to talk, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we weren't brutally abused, just told, and fortunately we hadn't to be told too often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And this would be by your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Or father, h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2167424\charrsid2688408 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 m. But we daren't do any other those days. Life were all like that among community that we lived in as far as I can remember. The congregational church people and school, you daren't speak}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2167424\charrsid2688408  out of your turn those days. It }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 isn't same as it is today, they're given too much free speech today, even amongst children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Never! Never, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents equally? Or from your mother more than your father, or your father more than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. Equally shared, between all t'family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. If it were a birthday there would be a cake made and a small present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, not as many as they have today, there'd happen be the odd one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Just occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
But no one could afford it in those days not in the working community. We only been talking about that this dinnertime amongst these friends that
 we've been looking at that photograph of, you know. People couldn't afford it. We got into our late 'teens before we started associating with ... going out to parties and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you remember how you spent Christmas Day with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Always spent it at home, and even after we were married we went back home as long as they lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have a traditional Christmas dinner and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 They couldn't afford such things as turkeys or chickens. It
 were mainly pork or beef. Plain, again. But it were nothing common, everybody were in same way in working families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you actually spend the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We spent the day like any other Christmas day with families. We got up in morning and looked
 at our toys and then we'd a Christmas dinner and then Christmas Day amongst ... all together, you see. But there weren't parties in those days, there weren't stuff to make parties of. There weren't the novelties that there is today. And if there were you
 couldn't afford them. It was very plain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Yes, we did. Me father always sang with the local choirs, Glee Unions and Chapel Choir and we'd a little harmonium in the house and they would spend a lo
t of their time before televisions and wireless inviting the chapel people up on a Sunday night and having a sing round this little organ. Not much in t'week, but weekends, particular Sunday night after chapel they would come, we'd sing round the organ. A
nd he eventually bought a flute and he tried to play that. And then later I fell for cornet playing in the brass bands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Between 1925 and '30, when I started to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But when you were at home as a child it was just the harmonium, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Harmonium, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did anybody else play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, no. There again, I can truly say that they weren't ... that they couldn't afford it and they weren't as much education ... piano tuition that there is today. All my children is going for piano lessons. My grandchildren, rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Only father, he were a chorister, Glee Union, and such like. And my mother an elocutionist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a child, did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, wit
h the exception that time were limited, again, you see. Then we played ourselves, but we ... always ... method of using the dart board, or table games}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2167424\charrsid2688408 , and they bought us, then, me}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 canos that you could make up of a night and that sort of thing and play, you
 see, yourselves. They mainly bought stuff we could entertain ourselves with, and I think your school life and our generation was that, you was learned to entertain yourself. Nowadays they're being entertained by that silly box, there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents play any outdoor games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, because ... that four years seems to me a long time in a person's life but I fell for football, local football. You see, a village like this in those days had at least 4 football teams, from leaving schoo
l Four football teams. There isn't one today. And there were two Sunday schools had 'em and then there were 2 village football teams, besides, and there were four teams in this one village alone. And all districts around had a similar number of teams and 
you could get a football league, or two football leagues in a town like Keighley. You can't get one today, because of that box and the motorcar. That's what I put it down to, meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have books in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, because again, mentionin
g the congregational church, we always had a prize-giving and we'd always get a book because we were well attenders and we never really missed the first prize, either of us. And it those days it were the old Chatterbox book which took you a long while to 
r
ead and to get through, and the games and stuff that was in it. The old Chatterbox Book, about 2 inch thick and they aren't making them a quarter of the size today for a lot more money, are they. And there was always the Bible. There again, me father went
 
to the congregational church, me mother spent the part time and we did, there was always the Bible and there were one book that they did advise us to read and that were the Pilgrim's Progress. I weren't a reader, meself. Me brother was a bigger reader tha
n me and me mother was a great reader. I don't think me father was. But those were the 3 principal books. They couldn't afford magazines that they can afford to buy today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about newspapers, did they have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I wouldn't say so, apart from the local paper at Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not a lot because they hadn't time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember a funeral in the family at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I only remember my grandmother ... two grandmothers. Not my grandparents but me 2 grandmothers. I remember them going to their funerals.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you remember anything much about it, how attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, I really can't, only the family, you see. Me father had 3 or 4 brothers. But money was 
scarce and they didn't have events even at a funeral like they've had recently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was the tradition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
The tradition of a funeral in those days were more or less you'd to walk to graveside. As a matter of fact I once remember one young fellow, 
and he was only a young fellow that died in this village and we carried him a quarter of a mile because of the expense. And it were more or less like that. You'd the hearse and then you would probably walk to funeral, but fortunately it were in the church
yard and we hadn't far to walk from the church, you see, and we didn't live so far from the church. But a lot of it in those days were like that, they'd to walk at back of the hearse and the hearse in those days were horse-driven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, they did as much as they could afford. As much as they could afford they went into mourning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How long did they stay in mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, within 12 months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a child were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends and relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
We'd our share of it, but mainly through the congregational church itself, with all its social activities, and its Sunday school walks and it's Sunday school trips and its ... and there were a lot of events in those days spent down at Sunday
 school because at that time this congregational church were built in 1912 and it cost }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2897202 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
2,000 to build and we'd it to pay off, and there was always a pie supper or a social, or some event three or 4 times a week went off. So we spent nearly all our life down there socially, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you, then, not taken out much by your parents as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, as much as they'd time for, again. Oh, yes, we kept together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Where would they take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, into local parks or local events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you taken shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, if we wanted to go, but we didn't always want to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that with your mother, or mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, mainly with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, I think we would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember outings, for instance Bank holiday outings, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Bank holidays, we'd always ... this week holiday, but at the beginning we'd only 4 days' holiday and we never missed, apart from the War years, going
 to Blackpool or Morecambe, you see, for the 4 days or a week. And in those days they'd to take all their own food. They didn't board in those days, they took their own food with them. Everybody. We were no exception, everybody did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go away the four of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
All four of them, until we become to the age of scouting and then there were them few years we went camping with scouts. The odd years, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you went to Blackpool what sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, there again, 
as much as you could afford. You were limited. You'd to play on sands, and you'd have the odd trip by the horse waggonettes in those days which weren't very far, were it. I mean, the horse waggonettes at the best in half a day didn't go about 4 or 5 miles
 round the town, you get a town like Blackpool. And we did do once or twice a week like that. And then we'd get to play on sands and walk about generally and spend what money we had, but that was limited, on other events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you spend your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, mainly locally, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go out playing about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Playing about locally and watching local football teams and cricket teams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Sunday was mainly Sunday school, wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, yes. And then Saturday n
ight, as I say, there was always something on at Saturday night at Sunday school. Well, we'd always Saturday evening taken up ... well, let's say 80% of time. And if we didn't go to Sunday school we'd got the odd chance of going to pictures. But pictures 
in those days, you know, there was only a couple or two to go to weren't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I imagine it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, it were, there were only a couple or 2. You could get fish and chips in those days for three 'a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2167424\charrsid2688408  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 pence. Fish and 'a'p'th they used to talk about and I don't think it were much more to go to local cinema. Silent pictures, sat on planks, not cushion seated.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 On Sundays you had your shoes then, didn't you, as opposed to your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As opposed to us clogs, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have a best Sunday suit and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you play games at all on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We used that same Sunday suit when it got done to wear during the week when it got tattered. And I'm not crying poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no. It was the thing then, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
It were the thing, it were the generation, and local, they are. Because in them early days a labourer ... well, some of the labourers only had 19 shillings a week. It's a fact, is that, before 1914 War, you know. And they were working 50 odd hou
rs a week for 19 shilling a week were some labourers in those days. 'Course, coal were 2/1 a bag, weren't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you play games at all on a Sunday or did your parents think that was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Definitely wrong. They kept Sunday to its Sunday, yes, they did. I will say that about my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And the same would apply about the notion of work on a Sunday, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no work done at Sunday, no! No newspaper then, much, either. No, for the working class family, as near as they could, they k
ept to the Sabbath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. Later years, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a child did you not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not as a child, no, I always sung in Sunday school event. I've sung Gilbert and Sullivan. In my 'teens I sung Gilbert and Sullivan and da
nced Horn Pipe and that sort of thing in Gilbert and Sullivan's 'Pinafore'. Sunday school events, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have a temperance club at the ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we had, but we never joined it because they called it Rechabites and that were run at our
 local congregational church, but we became Shepherds for some reason, I don't know why. Probably because me father associated with Shepherds. He were an Odd Fellow, himself, but later ... I think it were this way, that there was a gentleman in the congre
gational church, again, that were a Shepherd and he asked us to ... me father to put us in as youths. So we were she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12658438\charrsid2688408 pherds, he were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408  an Odd Fellow and that kind of thing, it just applied to people inviting you to join these things, whatever denomination or w
hatever friendly society it were. Later years I joined National Deposit for another because of somebody else recommended it, and I've been a Shepherd and a National Deposit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What actual clubs run by the church did you belong to? As a youngster. Or was it all informal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, it was all informal. Everybody threw in because, as I said, this place we'd to pay for after 1912 and in my generation and day, as a child that they'd to have so many social events that they were all family events, you all th
rew in. Bit of country dancing and a bit of games and that kind of thing. And pie suppers, plenty of pie suppers. Plenty good meals, and so me mother and plenty of people like 'em went down on a Saturday afternoon and rolled their sleeves up and made 'em 
so that everybody had a real good feed at a reasonable price, and mainly pie suppers, year in and year out. (laughter) You think of it, beef and potato pie, but it were a Yorkshire dish, I'm sure it must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was Grace said at meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Partly. Partly, but not regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And who would say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Father. But I've been in company and more \{BLANK\}
 where it has been done at table every meal. But we was ... time limited to those things beside. An hour to come home to get the meal and
 Mother to make it by that time and Father soldiering, again, and taking his dinners, you had to make do and mend with everything you did, you see. Hope all this sounds sense to you. It's quite correct what I'm telling you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you ever have family prayers together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, family ... Yes, family prayers together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, family prayers weren't regular, but prayers at bedside were. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What were his views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No more than a strong advocate of Labour Party. He thought he were a labour man himself and on principle he was a Labour man and a true Socialist. They aren't today, you know, even the Labour people aren't socialists today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about your mother, was she interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not entirely, no. No, not entirely. But me father yes. The first Labour M.P. that got up in Keighley ... the first ever Labour man
 got up in Keighley was a chap called Lee Smith, and he would bring him into village and he would stand him ... take him out of house and he would stand him on it in front of his own door. He weren't ashamed of doing that. And even he'd put rosettes into 
our pockets and into his when they were all wearing blue in this village, without being too strong on politics. But on principle he were a Labour man and a true socialist and if he'd a shilling he'd share it with next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would your mother be Labour, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Definite, she followed his ... oh, yes. We were very much a family life, as poor as we were, and not extremely poor. There were a lot of poorer folk in the area, but we fell in as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember your father and mother voting in an election? Before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes! They voted in all council elections and such like. When they were available, of course they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The first General Election that women could vote at was the 1918 election. Your mother would vote in that, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, she'd vote in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would it be the Labour Party that they would vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I definitely think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 In some places at that time people felt they might risk losing their jobs if they voted differently from their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 It was definitely so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did it apply at all do you think in the case ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
My father's principle was this: when we come to be working age we're not working at same place, none of us. We're all working 'cos we're not tying ourselves up with one
 another to be too dependent of other people. We'd all work at different places, and we did, you see. And he stuck to his principle and as I say would have given his last ha'penny. I've seen me father take his dinner our of oven at Sunday to give to peopl
e
 that were poorer than himself, particularly if they come far and nobody to make a meal for them. I've seen him take dinner out of oven and say 'we can manage, let them have it'. Honestly, he were one of the truest socialists ... I've known socialists wit
h a lot of money that's a lot more skinny than he ever knew how to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was your father actually a member of the Labour Party? Did he work for the party, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he do any canvassing at election time, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, he probably would help at local councils elections, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And what about your mother, would she help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, she'd never time, had she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, she wouldn't have. Did your father do anything at any other time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, I d
on't think so, no. No. My son's done more than we've ever done, been the public officer at elections. That isn't the right name for it, is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Are you talking about the agent for the Party, now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not the agent for the Party, but going into the polling booth and he's been the officer for the day there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Presiding officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Presiding officer, that's the right words, yes. My son's done a lot of that. 'Course, his time allows him to do it. He's in a bank, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, as I say, it were early to bed and early to rise in those days, and we would sit and talk, well ... bedtime, until bedtime and go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your mother have any interests outside her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Not part from Chapel. As I say, it were all spent down there, this place we'd to pay for, and friendly connections down there were tremendous and it were all spent down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did she ever go out just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no, not individually, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When your father was working locally what time did he get home in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Half past 5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Every ... all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would he ever attend a club or pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no. They'd neither time nor money for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 My father, no, apart from his little bit of music, choir singing and that's about what he did, and Chapel life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did he ever attend races, or did he ever have a bet on a ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, he'd no money and time, again, for things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The only savings club they could ever connect with were the holiday club at the congregational church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that for going away on an outing with the congregational church or was it to save up for ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, annual holiday. Annual holiday. And that, and the surplus for the annual holiday helped to pay the rates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You say that you and your brother found your own mates; did you get on well together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Very well. It is today, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you ever close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As close as one wants to be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a child who did you play with, was it neighbours' children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Neighbours' children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And where did you play? In the street playing football, you mentioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Street football; and then we'd a local corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12658438\charrsid2688408 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 mill down there. It were quite a village and a local corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12658438\charrsid2688408 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
mill, you know, everybody know them and they always allow us to to play in stables at night, you s
ee. After they'd done their journeys they'd be coming with the carters, they called the carters in them days, and then they'd the horses to come home and feed and bed up for the night, and I personally spent a lot of time down there in corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10363341\charrsid2688408 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 mill yard, and school yard. We were only a village community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 It was a sort of village within the town, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were there any particular games that you played as children when you were out? Any street games, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, we played all this noughts and 
crosses and football on street and the other one ... what did we call it? Dunce coming on. You would all get down and jump on one another's backs, and see how far you could jump over so many persons. And then a bit of local tree-climbing, like monkeys, fr
om tree to tree. We were a village, you know, you could do it. And you could play out in fields, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was your mother's attitude if you got dirty while you were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, it was a quiet attitude because she hadn't too much time to 
spend with us and she gave us a good clean-up when we got home. No chastising about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you free to play with anybody you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were there any children at all that your parents discouraged you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You say you belonged to the scouts later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were there any other youth organizations ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Me brother more than I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But you did belong, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I did join the scout movement, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you belong to any other youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, there wasn't many other ... apart from the church activities, there weren't you see, and as I say, the church activities were the whole family affairs in those days. But scouts, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any hobbies? Like keeping pets, or collecting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we always the odd rabbit, or white mouse, or something, that sort of thing. 'Till cat got 'em (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Stamps. Stamps, yes, stamp collecting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no, neither of us never went fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go for walks, or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
We did plenty of walks and plenty of bicycles .. My first bike that I were bought ... or I bought, it had cane rims. Do you ever remember them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And it had cane rims with wire spokes, of course, and it had the hub brakes, the block brakes that if you're going over ... do you know 
\{BLANK\} here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I don't really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, it's a fair good c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408 limb from \{BLANK\} over top to I}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 kley, by the time you got over the other side the brake blocks rubbed on the cane rims you nearly got on fire afore you got to bottom (laughter). But I've never seen one since, a cane rimmed bicycle.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 About what time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 1912 or '13.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As I got older, used to play football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Mainly. And 'course, there weren't football teams at school in them days. The only events that we had at day school were a trip down to Fire Station 
or the trip to museum once a year. There were no organised football teams at all. And we went ... they took us to swimming baths, but we'd to walk to Keighley a mile from school and walk back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go to any theatre or concert or music hall while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We did. We did if they were respectable, let's put it that way. But they were more respectable by a thousand times than they are today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, if we did go we went with our parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any pocket money as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we were limited to pocket money. We got our share as much as they could afford. We weren't left in cold, oh, no, we got our share.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 About how much would you get, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, it were coppers. You could get a lot for coppers in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was this regularly every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Not recognized, no. 'Course, they would pay for ... if they took us they would pay, you see. But the small amount that it cost to go to Sunday school events
 if they weren't with us, or to go to scouts and scout events, the small coppers it took they would give us all that sort of thing. But there were no recognized amount given.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What other sorts of things did you spend your money on? Was it mainly sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, there again, in 1914 War, which took a lot of my time up, there weren't many sweets to be got and at one particular time, what you would have got a penny'worth of sweets for, or a ha'p'th of sweets, the local shopkeeper were making a square a park}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408 ing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408  and you bought that sort of thing instead of \{BLANK\}
 But you could get ... a penny or three ha'pence, you could get any amount of sweets. You could, honestly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You've mentioned this sort of communal way in which people helped to prepare meals 
for each other: was there any other means by which neighbours helped one another in times of illness and things like that? Did your mother ever have any help from anybody if she was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 My mother and father never, 'cos they never needed it. They jus
t plodded along in their own simplicity and had just sufficient to manage with, but I'd've said they've done more for other people than they've ever had done for themselves, many times. In a small capacity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I mean actually helping to look after a hous
e rather than giving things, or anything like that. Did anybody outside the home help your mother if she was ill, for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, she never was ill. I never remember me mother being ill until her death, and she were just about a week, then. But s
he would go out at any time, and me father would an' all. Take a meal out or go do some'at for somebody in less circumstances than themselves. Both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, the next were a mile away, so we 
didn't get to see them above once a week and that were me grandparents ... one lot of grandparents. And Keighley market in them days were open 'till 10 o'clock at night and they would go, do their shopping after night because stuff were cheaper. And we'd 
s
tand round pea and pie stall and get a pie and peas, visit grandma, but she'd nothing to give us. But we'd get pie and peas and we'd come home with a lucky packet and ... And we'd have to walk to Keighley and back, that mile. And that were a Saturday nigh
t outing, except for Sunday school events, locally. And that were one year in and one year out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Scores of friends through Chapel. You see, we'd go to one another's houses as a family and sit round the organ. Or one
 family had these ... one of these here that came out, Pianola things. Well, that were a novelty for the period. Then gramophone came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents have the same friends, or did your mother have some of her own and your father ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, they shared them. They shared them, definitely. Mainly through the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When people came into your home did they come by invitation, or casually, or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And would they be offered something to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As much as they could give them they got something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would this be on particular days or occasions, or any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 They never went out without they got a cup of tea. And I've seen my father, if there were an old tramp in those days which you don't see 
today, do you? Tramp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
You don't see 'em today. But I've seen me father bring a tramp in and say 'now then, Mother, make him a cup of tea and give him a sandwich'. A pot of tea and a sandwich. There weren't many cups of tea in
 them days. A pot of tea. And I've seen me father do that. I'll tell you on principle I don't know another, because we were extremely limited for finance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did neighbours come in and out of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 They'd no need to do because they were ... me mother were healthy, you see, she didn't need it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I meant socially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, they came in socially, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And did your mother and father go in neighbours' houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 There were no enemies in family. No, we were all friends. You couldn't carry
 a Christian life and work in a Christian community and be fair than do any other way, could you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
You've mentioned these sing-songs and musical to-doments that your parents had with their friends, did they have any other way of making their own amusements when they got together, do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, again, through the church and all, although we were limited for space with just one room and a kitchen, the Chapel people would have private ways and means of getting money together and they would have
 a little pie supper, a little community get-together limited to the number they could invite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 In the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And from one house to another they would go there over a time, you see. It were quite a village life. My grandchildren is missing that to
day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You've spoken of yourself as belonging in those days to a sort of respectable working class family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Definitely. I'll put it further than that: a poor, respectable family. And it takes something to be poor and respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did you see the different social classes being in the days before 1918, in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, the social classes were extremes. Absolutely extremes, but I would say they were 90% working classes in a village like ours, and the odd 5% were the extremists, y
ou see. The mill owners - I always contended that the village ... church minister in the village and the station master that used to be dripped in golden braid in those days, and the village doctor and squire - that were it. And the mill owner. And apart 
f
rom them you were all working class section. There were just one row of houses in village where the community managers lived in. The block of houses is there today, but they aren't all managers that lives in them today. They've separated from as far as go
i
ng to Harrogate and coming back to work every day, now. That distance, with cars, you see. But in those days it were a community that lived in one section of a block of houses and all managers lived down that block. And then mill master ... to mill master
s in village, station master, and church vicarage. And apart from them all the others were working class community. And they were a working class community, without a doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you come into contact at all with the top notches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, only again 
through church life, you see, we met 'em all. I were only talking to a solicitor the other day at a funeral that I were at and ... you see our church were an offspring off another church in Keighley, congregational circuit, you see, and on all the big eve
n
ts, same as prize-giving or anniversaries, or any big event at all, they would invite these people to come and open them, and we met 'em in that respect. And we got pretty close to 'em. 'Course, of later years we got closer still to 'em. But I think the b
ig people 'as come closer to us, too. I'm sure they have. I'm sure they have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. We'd to treat 'em all alike or else don't bother with them. But we bothered with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, to raise your hat, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 To who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, to older people than ourselves, mainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 To older people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Older people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Rich or poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Rich or poor, because I believe me father didn't think there was so much difference between him and best of men. And I don't think so, today. What can one do more than go out to his work and work 50 year consciously, and I'd only 5 years' sickne
ss in all me life. What can one do and achieve more than that in any age? And he could do no more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
than go serve his country as he did and were wounded and disability. Well, what difference is there between the top and the bottom, only finance. And I think 
that's comed a lot nearer to us than ever it were in those days. It were outstanding in those days, you know. I'll tell you a tale, shall I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, you do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 About a local manufacturer that lived in this estate here, where grammar school is today. A
t the end of that block of houses is grammar school and there this house that this mill master lived in is still there and the new modern grammar school is built on to it. The old house is sort of annexed to the grammar school. And he'd 3 daughters and he
 
used to come walking down every Sunday morning, down Ingrow Lane, and he didn't walk on Casually him and his 3 daughters and his wife - this is when I were a child - he didn't walk on Casually but there were no traffic in those days, you see. And he said 
... his statement were, he said when they were kidding him about his daughters not getting married, he said 'well, you see, shoes won't come and clogs daren't'. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 That's a neat way of putting it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Aye. When he wanted his daughters married
 he said 'shoes won't come and clogs daren't. Well, that's what he thought of life. And even that firm went bankrupt, or partly, anyway. I've seen in my time, I've seen one of the biggest man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408 
ufacturers in this country go b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 ankrupt, and associating with him. And he did that through being too generous with local events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was this in the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
And of course, trade depression ... trade depression, in '20s. Trade depression, and being too easy-going and giving too much away socially, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 In the early days was there anybody that you called 'sir', or 'master' or 'madam'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We were always learned to talk that ... we were always taught to talk that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 To anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 To a school ... no, to schoolmasters or anybody older, again, you see. Anybody that you would naturally respect.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember people showing respect to your parents in ways of this kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that because of their association with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Me father had Military Medal, for
 one thing, and he'd certificate with odd fellows, you know, framed, and highly respected as a person throughout ... all his social abilities throughout, respected as a person. And he had these odd things which showed it, like, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What sort of p
eople would the employers, for instance, associate with in their social life? You say this particular mill man with his daughters ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Associated mainly amongst their own ; class. But as you know, that ... at golfing, particularly, and they were the p
eople to introduce sport at Sunday ... without a doubt ... nobility ... but in the olden days it were family life with them. And occasionally once a year or for ... not one week, but two or 3 weeks a year they would go up into Scotland and the places 'cos
 
there were farmers up there, you see, and they would ... We'd 2 big mill owners in Keighley, one sponsored a Wesleyan chapel which were close, and the other sponsored the Church of England, and that's in this village, and we were a congregational Free Spe
e
ch place, were a working man's institution, you know. And I've seen at Whitsuntide walks when there's been a band playing for all 3 walks and we've clashed in village as bands matched past. And they would all go ... the Church of England people would go t
o
 Haggas's and the Wesleyans would go up to Clough's and we would go into us own field. But apart from that, even in the aristocracy as you could call them in those days it were a village community, because you'd no things as cars, you see, to get 'em away
.
 There were only their ways and their own carriage and pairs and they didn't take 'em so far, did they. I mean, I worked on Clogh's firm when they were all horses, carriage and pair, they'd a stable full of carriage horses and a stable full of working hor
ses. They went to Bradford with the goods by horses daily. The old wagons went with the goods to Bradford every day. So they couldn't get so far, could they. They couldn't get so much further than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would you say that any particular class associated 
outside its own class? I'm thinking of, say, clergy or teachers or farmers or shopkeepers. Would they associate with others of their own kind or would they mix more freely with the community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, there again, you see, there were farmers, besides mi
ll owners, both of them and naturally they'd have their own local butchers shop, you see, which they would go get the meat at this particular one shop. And the groceries were same way. They'd have their own ... I don't think they were co-operative people 
or anything like that, you see. That's come up from private co-ops in my time to a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408 ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 lgamated co-operative societies, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were there small shopkeepers about in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, they were all small shopkeepers. Matter of fact there were one lo
cal co-operative society, private co-operative society that paid their own dividen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12939491\charrsid2688408 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
 and run their own affairs and quite a small shop no bigger than ... half as big again as this house. You see, and they would trade with them. And local butcher. That's all they could do. And of course they grew their own vegetables, didn't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What sort of people were the small shopkeepers? Did they mix freely with all and sundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes. Oh, yes. Yes, they were local people and ... To start with they were loc
al people in those days when I were young, they were all local people, local families that run 'em. Local family that run this co-op. Manager were, anyway. And anybody went to shop that wanted, it were open shop to anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about the clergy, did they associate freely with people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Yes, but I think in those olden days, as me as a youth, I think the Church of England particularly ... well, I think Minister were on a higher status than what they are today. As I pointed out before, the squire, th
e station master and the vicar and the mill master were the four of five quality people in village. But today, I think it's shameful today that the minister to minister undo people, that's brought into a church to minister unto the people hasn't a working
 man's wage today. I know that. I think it's shocking, don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 It is, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
They bring them in to minister unto 'em and they can't afford to pay 'em only a minimum wage. So their status has gone down. That is one status that's gone down, as min
ister, in the standard of living. You see, all these old rectories, well, they were a massive size, so massive today that if you go into 'em today they're so poverty-stricken, they can't afford to keep 'em going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Could you see any difference between the sort of people that went to the Church of England and the sort of people that went to your church?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, yes! Yes, you got ... As I say again, we were a working community belonged to a respectable community, but poor, the poorer class. But the peopl
e that went to the Church of England, and the church that went to Wesleyan Chapel thought ... they were more bosses in industry, you see, bosses in the families than what we were. But we got, as years went on we got closer together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was there a Catholic Church at all about, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, nearest Catholic Church were in town, you see. It were the only one. St. Anne's. I didn't know much about that as a child, but later they built a fine church just down here, St. George's, and of course, every vil
lage you go into now has Catholic Community which has extended tremendously at side of non-conformists. Without a doubt they're shoving non-conformists into ground, but they're ready to co-operate with you. I only asked one of the Catholic priests here to
 
come and give us a talk with week .... On Monday night I asked him to come and give us a talk at our men's fellowship which I wouldn't've dared to have done years since, they seemed to be unapproachable. We seem to be getting nearer. Apart from politics, 
apart from status in life, I think people are getting a little bit nearer. Don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I'm sure. I think they're getting more dependent on one another, and all. I think they are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would you say that all the people in the working class had the same standard of living? Or were there different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, the only reason that they hadn't a standard of living were the parents that went out drinking, gambling, and all other vices of life. Well, my parents didn't do that. Al
though they were probably same income as a labourer, that made the difference. We'd a home ... a respectable working-class home, where if you went into these homes they hadn't a home to go into.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you know any family like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, with any un ... disrespect for Clough's ... Did you go in a Clough's yard mill yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, Clough's mill is right in centre of this valley, just down there, right in centre and at each side up valley there's five blocks of terrace houses and they belong to firm. Now, this side of village there's a similar sort of blocks ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You were telling me about the two rows of houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. The two rows of houses, you see, the community in this village were built up round manufacturing and each manufact
urer had his own working class houses. There'd be two, to 3 or 4 hundred houses round these two mills. Without any amenities, and all. Just stone floors, again, no hot and cold water, no toilets inside, having to walk a hundred yards to a toilet, you see.
 
Up 'till recently, this, this last year or two. And a lot of the people that lived in 'em were drinkers and gamblers and weren't like what I've been telling you about my parents, and that small difference enabled my parents to buy their own house and even
tually put these amenities in. Well, they deprived themselves of doing that because they lived such a silly life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you think in those days that one group felt itself superior to the rest within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 There were 3 standards, and the
y definitely were apart. There were the manufacturers themselves, then there were the foremen and their families which thought ... once they put them a yellow coat on they thought they were it, and then there were the working classes. But there were defin
i
tely a division between the three parties. Definitely. Both in church life, social life and even in sporting life, 'cos they would even seek their own sport where they thought it were a bit better. And of course, if they've more money they could afford to
 do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, by Jove, aye! Oh, aye. There was some real rough families in them days. But they were big families, you know. There were no ones and twos in those days, there were sevens and eights, and up to 1
0. Well, a working man ... it took some bringing up and keeping respectable, if they tried. They were bound to be rough. And they were both rough and tough, and the peculiar thing about it were that more they were kicked about stronger persons they were. 
I
f a child were pampered and petted it were more of a weakling than what they were. That's my experience of what I saw in life. Honestly, I'll be frank, I believe in plain living and as big a families as there were living without any amenities at all only 
stone floors and just bedroom space and many a time went to sleep in drawers, cupboard drawers, as children. They were brought up tougher and more reliable, although they were tougher and rougher, they were more reliable, you know. They were, honestly.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember a distinction being felt between trained draftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Definitely, and in my young days even to go and be an apprentice. All trades and crafts people were distinctive in their clothing. Funny thing, but you could tell 'em
 all in the clothing: the butcher, the baker, the undertaker, the cabinet maker, and all the lot of them, they'd all distinctive method of clothing. If it were only a corduroy pair of trousers, or undertaker with his tall hat and dark coat on, or butcher 
w
ith his striped overall and sorter with his bray, that were a checked bray, and outside worker with his corduroys and ... They were all distinct in their clothing. It were funny, but they were. I've remarked about it many a time. You don't see it today be
c
ause industry today is different, there's no ... there isn't much stonework going on today, like monumental masons or stonemason or quarry work, is there. The undertaker, he's just a cloth suit on, today, he doesn't bother with tall hat and dark coat, doe
s
 he. And they were all distinct, in their clothing. And if one tradesman thought he were a little bit better off than the other he let you know it, and all. But doesn't that principle count today with unions? That's what we're up against. They're trying t
o narrow gap between wages and unions and they can't. They're still widening. But the trades unions today is trying to bring 'em together but they're still distinct, and they'll never get over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Me mother just thought she belonged to her own class, and outside of that she didn't try to be any different. That's the point. They tried to be different to what they are, and they aren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was it possible in those days for people to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, it were harder than what it is today. Of course, I put that down to better education, you see. Education's narrowed that gap. Definitely. As I were talking to you this morning, my nephew is 
teaching at King's College, Cambridge, you wouldn't've thought about that at one day and age. He's a nice young fellow, you know. But education's done that. Modern amenities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 There weren't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember anybody at all who did? Who did move up in those days, in the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 In stages, yes. You know the great Asa Briggs, historian? Well, I remember him going from a grammar school, if you mean from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was his a working class home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, I think so,
 yes. Yes. Yes, there's been a few in my day and age, but Asa Briggs is younger than me. And he would come to our place and give us a sermon. Oh, yes, we have two chancellor of exchequers that come from ... Iain Mcleod from \{BLANK\}
 just outside of here, the other week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, but I meant earlier on, talking about back ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But they brought theirselves up, but of course, Ian McLeod weren't so old, but ... Who were the Labour Chancellor of Exchequer that \{
BLANK\} yonder? That were more when I were a 
lot younger, what did they call him? First Labour Chancellor of Exchequer. They weren't ... they'd be that little bit better off but they weren't, they wouldn't be big money people, I don't think. What did they call him? I forget his name, now. Cowling. H
e lived at Cowling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember anybody being described as 'a real gentleman' or a 'real lady' when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. But do you know, again, I can truly say this I found it more out of the commoner people than the bigger people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
I did. They'd have due respect for everybody and willing to do anything for everybody and were respected by everybody through doing it. That isn't money. That isn't money, it's the people and their principles of the people that do that. I hope
 I'm not boring you to death. But I've experienced that through the congregational church and associating with other churches and other societies that I've met, you see. Highly respectable people, but there's many in the poorer classes as what there's bee
n in the bigger classes. Because the bigger class has it to do with and the people that you can respect that hasn't it that they can do these kind things is ... 'course they're more thought about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Yes. That's the point today, again. That the local policeman were the local policeman and you saw him every day and every night. Today you never see one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did you think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, he respected you, as they do today
, if you respected them, but if you didn't respect him he'd just give you one with his cape across face, and that were it. He wouldn't do no talking, he'd just give you clout across face with his cape. And, of course, we were a village, again, and all thi
s here ... there were these two estates and they would go apple-pinching at night, you know, lads' tricks you knew, and he would just chastise you with doing that, a clout with his cape and that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you were naughty did your mother ever say she'd call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, I don't remember that, no. If it were spoken in that respect it weren't spoken meaningfully, it were just jokingly. No, we never had now like that. We never had no need for it, never. I mean, I never did anything ... I 
mean, it isn't boasting, but we didn't dare ... we'd parents that we could look up to and they told us, if you make your own bed you lie on it. That were one quotation that they did from being a youth and it's installed into my life and it's still there t
oday, I wouldn't have quoted it if it hadn't' a been, would I. You see, and if you make your own bed you lie on it. And I can go anywhere today in all communities of life that I've been in, and still go back. And all people can't do that, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you were a child was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Us home were rented, and the first house that me mother and father had ... I'll tell you this, this were at Oakworth as a child. It were a farm cottage but it were a farming community in those days. It isn't 
much better, now. It's at top of hill, here, is Oakworth, do you know it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And the house that they rented were 4/6 a week, plus rent and milk found. Eggs and milk found, for 4/6 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And what about the house at Ingrow? That was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 That were rented, but that wouldn't be much more than 4/6 a week. I've known score of houses in Ingrow without ... less than 4/6 a week.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes. 'Cos I'm telling you, this village community where I was ... we'd two mill-masters, weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. Did your house belong to one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, never because neither my parents nor I got one, because they didn't work for them. Me mother did but me father didn't. And then when we went to work, b
oth me and my wife, we didn't work at same place, they'd these houses but they told us they were for families so I saved enough to buy me own and I've kept me own ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But the house you lived in at Ingrow ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were rented through a private landlord ... small private landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did you feel about him as a landlord, was he all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, it were all right, but it were same in those days as it is today that the landlord, he make it a speculation and he wanted all he could out
 of it. You couldn't get anything done. I imagine you can get less done today with the price of jobs being paid for, you can get less done. And some people hasn't sense to just save up a little bit and put theirselves on their own feet like I am here. I m
e
an, this is nothing, but it's comfortable, and I can spend money here, yet, and will do, and intend doing. I don't want to leave here, but only to be reasonable, when I've hand it on to somebody else, I hope so. But that's the project of life ; coming int
o life ... me father used to say come into life and try to leave something when you go out for somebody else, you see. Now, we can't say that about everybody. They want all there is and leave nothing for nobody else. It's just like that. You agree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, I do, yes. You felt that your parents had really to struggle to make ends meet, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, definitely because, as I said, they'd these here 14 weeks of out of work and no dole. No dole in them days, you know. But I never remember them struggling 
so much that they ... I never remember having to go for public assistance. It weren't called public assistance then, it were the old ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 The old Guardians. Nothing like that in family, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did you feel about this struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, we'd to live through it, hadn't we? We'd to learn to live with it, you see. There were no trouble about it, we just had to learn to live with it, and we did do, you see, as a family. It were no trouble to us, only, as I
 said, me father were always trying to achieve stuff out of his own small limits, and living quite a respectable life and gaining the odd copper or two and some way of spending it to make a difference, and quite a few round the family were same way, uncle
s and aunts. That's the only difference I could see, that difference being one being a little bit more careful with same amount as what the others are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Before you went to school were you given lessons at all by anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Three and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 That was young, wasn't it. When you first started did you go for all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, I think I would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What sort of school hours were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Nine 'till 12 and one o'clock 'till 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What sort of a school was it that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Just an ordinary council school, run by local education in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get there, was it far away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, it weren't five minutes off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And you would walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We walked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 It were so near we went ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, but I mean did your brother go with you, or did you go with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, we would toddle on together with other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You went home for your dinner, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, because in those days they didn't provide school meals, they didn't even provide milk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did you think about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, me in particular, I weren't of an educative nature and I just struggled through, mediocre, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I didn't dislike it because there were certain things made up for bad things, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I always thought they were very nice, the teachers, very nice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did they emphasise certain things as being important? You know, things like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, always. Always, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Always, but as I told you, they were limited to what they could advocate because people hadn't it to do with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What about ways of speaking, were they concerned about ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Not as much as they are today. That's why we still ... my grandchildren laughs at me because you can't
 get out of the old Yorkshire dialect - 'owt can happen and nowt can happen' it's surprising, my youngest grandson hasn't gone to school, he starts this next term, but he ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2383998\charrsid2688408 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408  pull me up now with dialect. But it weren't stressed at all, weren't that. Unders
tand, at school we'd only a ... biggest part of my schooling days down here we'd only a school slate with a wood frame round it to do us writing on, and mathematics and we were strictly limited to mathematics, English and reading, weren't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 If you did something the teachers disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Tell us to kneel down at side of desk and give us a clout with book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was that the regular form of punishment or did they use any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, they had the cane, but it were a sc
hool with a good reputation, I must say that. Looking back on it all it must have had a very good reputation, apart from that I told you about 6 me father going and saying 'if they deserve it give 'em it', which were never used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was there very little physical punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Very little, very little, I don't remember ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was there any other sort of punishment, you know, standing in corners and being kept in after school and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, there were that sort of thing, yes. B
ut a very small amount of it. Very small. Quite a respectable village community and we all knew one another, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were girls punished the same as boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, there weren't a lot of punishment, I wouldn't quite just say as I had, but there were very little in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What sort of offences would merit punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, well, there weren't much, but if there were any lifting or anything like that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Pilfering, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Pilfering, you see, they'd just bring 'em in, and if ther
e were any grumbles about local damage they'd tell schoolmaster, you see, and he'd do what he could. One lad, he had a bird one time and he stuck it with pins all over, I remember at school, well he were chastised for that, you see. Catched the bird and p
inned it. Bits of things like that you can remember but generally speaking ... As I say, with a village community and they all knew one another ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, as much as they could, but they hadn't time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, we got our school reports, you see and they were interested in them, but we couldn't hope to be anything but ordinary craftsmen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents visit the school at all, or meet your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 There again, there weren't open days like there is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did all the other children come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did the teachers single out any of them for different treatment from the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any gangs, or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, you may have had, like meself, 3 or 4 tough lads who were, you know, tried to be boss over other four and that sort of thing, but not unduly too much. But you get that ... it's a bit of human nature is that, i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2383998\charrsid2688408 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 n't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I always feel sorry in my life for infirmity amongst children. If they'd any infirmity, bad eyesight or cripples, they're bound
 to be left out, aren't they. Any normal child all through my life, and certainly now - they can do a lot more for them now, they didn't do much in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any children with infirmities or disabilities in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You had the odd
 one, hadn't you, like. I mean, I saw one young feller ... well, he isn't a young feller, now, in hospital the other week I went to see a friend across in another bed, that went to school with us, and he'd always irons up his legs, well he couldn't act sa
me as we could, you see. And I think they've a big disadvantage in life when they want respecting and they want helping, these people. See what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you go on to another school after that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No, I went to one school from the infants up into adult school and I were there all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Twelve
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, because of simple reason, like a lot more families they couldn't afford 
it. They wanted you to go to your work, and it applied in big families, did that. Get a lot of it in a big family, a lot of the old ones had to go out to work and then when it got a bit better off some of the young ones could go to an high school. That's 
happening this day and age, see. But people, ... I've known people ... I've had friends that's passed to go to grammar school and they couldn't afford to let 'em go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you attend any part time education after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Two years night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Mathematics and woodwork and English, but that's all they offered in them days. There were no science in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Never. Because I always seem to have ... I've had the ability to stand up for meself in all respects, without expecting too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, certainly would. But I think this: that a child learns more when he's left school than he does at school. 
I mean, a child leaving at a normal leaving age, he learns more after he starts reading for himself, local newspapers, than what he did at school, but he must 've got his bearings at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 While you were at school did you have a part time job? Or a means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I never had, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you left school was that to start full time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 First 12 months you went half time, but that were everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What was your job as a half-timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I went to a shuttle-making place, then I went into two textile industries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 All as a half-timer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, no. As a half-timer, textile. No, corn mill first time. Corn mill for first few months. Aye, it were corn mill that I went part time, and then after I went f
ull time into textiles, that were it. It were corn mill. It were 1914 and it were owing to shortage of labour and I were a strongish lad and he thought I were just what he wanted and I went, you see, only me and another fellow went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Let me just get this sequence of jobs straight. You went into the corn mill as a half-timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Yes, owing to 1914 and labour being short he asked me to go work for him, you see. I mean, they wouldn't've wanted me if there'd been plenty of manpower, you see what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. The whole of the time you were a half-timer you were working at this corn mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Corn mill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And that was for 12 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What did that entail? A week of mornings at work and afternoons at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And the other way round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, alternate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What hours did you work? When you were working in the mornings, say, what time did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 From 6 o'clock in the morning 'till 12. That were 6 hours. And then I think we worked Satu
rday mornings, I'm not sure about this, but I think we worked Saturday mornings included both weeks. It mightn't've done, it might have been one Saturday in a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 For simple reason that we knew him as a local bus
inessman, you see, and he knew family, and labour were so short he got so stuck that he asked me to work if I'd go for him, and I'd no other ... I'd nothing else in me head and I took it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 All there is to do in a corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid875350\charrsid2688408 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 mill, grinding corn and weighing it and measuring it out in two hundredweights and half c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid875350\charrsid2688408 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
ts. And loading and unloading, and all there was to do in a corn mill, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any holidays at all while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Only had me annual holiday, that would be at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Paid or unpaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Unpaid! Oh, they don't pay you them days!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What were you paid as a half-timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I would think somewhere between ten shilling and a pound, somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 As a half-timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you feel that that was a fair wage in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We didn't give it any thought at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I give it all to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did it go into the general family budget or was it put for one special purpose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, put into family ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you get any of it back as pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We may'a got about half a crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get on with the other people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I only worked with one man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, I see, just the employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Owing to labour ... No, he were employed by the employer, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel that the employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, as a small businessman, as well as you could expect, because they'd enough for themselves. A sma
ll businessman - and it's been like it all my life I've worked for them - I've worked for two firms in a small way, then I went into two big firms and I've noticed it all my life that the smaller people, business people is trying to get all out they can t
heirself, they're bound to do, to make ends meet. We had a case this week in local paper, Bradford paper, that there's hundreds of school-leavers that's not going to be able to find jobs 'cos a lot of these small trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid875350\charrsid2688408 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 people can't afford to take 'em in. Have you read that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well I read local Telegraph and that's been only this week, a lot of small engineering firms and such like that can't afford to take apprentices and there's going to be a lot ... hundreds of youths in Bradford that they ca
n't find jobs for this term, because they can't afford to take 'em in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But your employer, you felt he treated you all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, as much as he could. Much as he could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel about the work? Did you like it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Y
es, it were all right. I didn't leave 'till he couldn't find me enough to do. I only left because he couldn't find me enough to do and then another employer sat in office talking to him, he said 'well, will you come to work for me', and when I went to wor
k for him it were so crude with his methods. There were father and two sons in this business at time, and there again, they were wanting all plunder themselves, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Was this the shuttle-making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Shuttle-making, yes, and they were ... to my m
ind they were wanting it all for themselves and their families and they couldn't afford to pay any more but the amenities and facilities that they had were shocking. Very little ventilation and it were partly woodwork and partly steelwork and be 10 o'cloc
k
 in morning fumes and dust were blowing about you couldn't see across floor for it, and that were lack of ventilation. It were a place that were run with the old watermill, which electric power came on after, so that the conditions in those days weren't g
o
od, you know. But when I did decide to leave ... I did six months, but when I did decide to leave ... This was at 13 year old. When I did decide to leave they offered me half a crown a week, make a man of me but I couldn't see it in them days. Anyway, I w
ent to firm that I've left and they gave me round 15 1/2 to decide whether I want to stop at this particular trade, you see. And eventually I stopped and did 50 year with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 This was at Clough's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, but they'd all amenities there, and all fa
cilities. Expense were nothing to 'em. And eventually I finished up on superannuation with 'em, which is a grand thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 This shuttle-making job, what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, if I'd'a stopped long enough I'd've had to learn a bit of woo
dturning and boring and spindle-making to go into the shuttles ... all that comprised making a shuttle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But what did you actually do while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Partly machine work and partly hand work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Were they similar sort of hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes. It were all 6 o'clock in morning 'till half past 5 at night in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And Saturday mornings 'till half past 11.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get on with the other people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, very wel
l with everybody. Very well. It were just I couldn't see ... I got to that age I couldn't see any enlightment in it at all. I couldn't see any getting on. It wasn't the job for me, if I put it in that respect, and I left 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 So you went to Clough's then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Just applied ... Well, aunt of mine applied for me and I got in ... but I went into manufacturing side for a start. You see, into mill, as a lad and then they asked me to take this apprentice job where 
they made their own skips and baskets, you see. They'd their own department for skips and baskets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What were you doing in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I like all youth, \{BLANK\} We did what they call 'taking-off'. Taking the full bobbins off and putting the e
mpty ones on to re-start, and you do it ... you might get on a big frame with 150 spindles, you might get 10 youths like that, all doing about 10 a piece, taking about 10 a piece off, and you empty new ones ... put empty uns on and take full 'uns off. But
 nowadays it's all altered, it's all mechanical doffing, now. T'isn't hand doffing, it's all mechanical doffing, you see, but it were all hand doffing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 What were you paid there? A similar sort of wage, or better than you'd had before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 It'd be roughly about 3 or 5 bob a week, I think, then, as a lad, aye. What were it? 56 hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you get on with the other people there? Did you get on well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Very well, but in a community like that, you know ... I went in as a l
ad and I noticed one day there was a bit of jealousy cropped up and two or 3 of the other lads in same room put a letter in my pocket - I were a stranger to 'em, you see, and never been in a mill before - and they put in my pocket a note 'Beware of the Bl
a
ck Hand Gang'. So we sorted this out and we had a little bit of a scrap between us, 'till overlooker separated 'em, but they all three worked round me and bust me nose, and that, and he straightened them up, did overlooker. But the funny thing about that,
 
one's been in prison all his life ever since, one hung himself before he were 21, and some 'at happened to the other lad. So you can tell what sort of a community they were. If you want that tale, I don't know. But that were like that. And then it all wen
t on snugly after that. But you do m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3872994\charrsid2688408 eet that. Life isn't all smooth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
. But very little to bother about, but that were the first instance I met there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel about the work itself that you were doing at that time? Did you like it, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, all them jobs, all youth that went into industry at that time, all youth ... and it's more or less the same today, it weren't interested. You were waiting 'till time when you got into a better opportunity to do some'at better, you see. Apprenticeshi
p, and that sort of thing, and got a trade into you. But you'd, from 12 year old to 16, to do all rough work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 So you became an apprentice, then, at skip making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 At 16. Acknowledged at 16.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And you then carried on doing skip making all your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Fifty years, yes. Just 50 year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You were with Clough's all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 All the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How did you feel about Clough's as an employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I'd all respect for them. I told them ... my words when I finished with them and the
y called me in for an interview and told me what I had to come, I said 'well my words isn't good enough to explain what you've done for me, and that's respect for all the years I've been here'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would you have preferred another type of occupation than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, yes. I'd another three apprentices in my period. I'd four apprentices in my period under me. One's carrying on job as he is now, a married man, like, he's done 25 years, you see, with firm now. But the other 3 came in - this is younger ge
neration, again - the other 3 came in: one could see it were no job for him. I mean, he saw all these other outside trades coming on; plumbers, painters, electricians, you know, that Clough's were bringing in to do work for them, in their little motorcars
 
and vans, and he weren't going to be confined into one place. If you understand my job were just in a small compartment, confined in there all t'time. It were like the old cobbler in his own shop all day long from morning to night, you see, and these 3 yo
u
ths couldn't see that. They couldn't see that, so they left. They did 6 months and they left us. No due respect to me we couldn't hold 'em. Clough's said to me 'encourage 'em and give 'em what they want'. But you couldn't 'old 'em. One left in that respec
t
 ; one left through family reasons. He come out of North of England - his sister got him down here from his mother, his mother were separated in North of England and he came down and his sister working in mill and her husband and they asked if he could co
m
e in as apprentice and we took him. And he went up 6 months after to a holiday up home and when he got home his mother cried for him to stop. She's got in possession of Council house in her name, then, you see. So we lost him that. He came through family 
r
easons and he went through family reasons, you couldn't avoid that. The other lad left because he couldn't see no opportunity confined in one place. And the third went out of shop and I said, 'this lad ...' I could see I couldn't make a skip maker out of 
him. I couldn't see any possibility of making a skip maker out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3872994\charrsid2688408  of him and I give him no dis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
encouragement at all but when he walked out of shop I said to the other youth, I says, 'that lad'll get himself into trouble', and within a few weeks' time he got in 
a gang and he hit a taxi driver back of head with an iron bar. Well, I've never heard anything about him since. So there were 3 apprentices that I couldn't hold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 But would you, yourself, have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well that were the question you asked me, weren't it, in first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, looking back at it now I think I'd be of same idea as the first youth. I wouldn't confine meself to one place. I'd see more the life for getting out. I've a nephew now that workin
g for one of the biggest tool firms in keighley, engineering, and he's been brought up as a tool maker, he's a good craftsman, but they've appointed him this last few years as travelling all over England and Ireland and Scotland, provided car. He goes to 
u
niversities, he goes to prisons, he goes to colleges and he goes into factories just to overhaul them machines, you see. And he can't spend much time with them because he hasn't time in days that he goes, but he puts them machines right while he's there. 
A
nd I think I would prefer the adventure of life to confining meself in one room if I had me time over again. That's all, but I'd have had to look our for remuneration, and all, at the end of it and knowing what I know now. All my years at Clough's I didn'
t
 think about remuneration at all, honestly, and I were 58 before they called me into office to give me superannuation. Two year older and I wouldn't have got into it because the insurance companies wouldn't've accepted it, but they back-dated me and made 
i
t right, you see. Now, I've learnt that since, I never gave it a thought before. But knowledge that I have now I would've had to seek remuneration for ... like any other person. You see what I mean? And I'd've moved for adventure and remuneration, which I
 never gave it a thought in my day and generation. I thought ... when I were a lad you were lucky to get a trade. You were jolly lucky to get a trade, to be respected as a tradesman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you belong to any trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, because I were i
solated, you see. I were isolated in industry that I worked in. I was an outside trade in an industry, you see, as a skip maker. If I'd been direct in textiles I would have been obliged to be in trade union, but I weren't. And Clough's respected it and I 
respected them. We did all right. But that wouldn't apply to 9 out of 10.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same outlook, or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, because I tell y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3872994\charrsid2688408 ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 , it's nature again for each side to look after themselves. You can't get away from nature, you try, you try what you like. Nature's a funny thing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. To be frank, no, there weren't collaboration that one could expect. No. I've 
just told you an instance, haven't I? A small incident. Mind you, it weren't too set apart, but it just weren't the full co-operation that one could have expected. And I do think there is today, we wouldn't be having all this trouble today if it were like
 that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Some people say that in those days there was this great distinction between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that in your works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I did in beginning. In olden days, definitely, but I think the gap's narrowed there. But circ
umstances has altered things. Because when I were a lad, apprentice, him I served me time with he served at 28 shillings a week against chaps having 26 shillings a week, but over years it's gone swung the other way so in a balance of years one contradicts
 
the other. What used to be a good craftsman today is in lesser degree, more so where industries has gone down, old crafts. There's valuable crafts, today, and valuable craftsmen that aren't getting money against unskilled persons today in some industries.
 You know what I mean? But in me young days there were this difference between craftsmen and ... but today balance has swung all ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Would you say that starting full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, I don't think that made much difference. That bit of half-time, you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, that didn't make no difference. It were easier on work people, weren't it, like. I mean, they put school-leaving age up opposed to that, didn'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3872994\charrsid2688408 t they, so it's better today, Is}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 n't it? W
e think it is, anyway. Opposed to having to go, 12 year old and working half time, I wouldn't know how to balance it between school - leaving age today and then. I mean, they're getting advantage, aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Do you think that that last year at schoo
l when you were at school half the time and at work the other half, do you think that you benefited educationally at all from it, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, because I'll tell you this: it were in corn mill as I'm telling yer and I know that I'd work form 6 o'clock 
in the morning 'til 12 and then I went in in afternoon, I once or twice were falling asleep and teacher says, 'let him go'. And in that day they didn't bother as much, they hadn't the facilities and they hadn't amenities to give you education like they ha
ve today. If they kept you well and happy that were all they bothered about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents at all, or with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, no, no. There's always been that little bit of ... slight jealousy between
 me and him because I finished up better than him. But you can't avoid it, can you. I restrain from telling him all my benefits. Frightened to do because I didn't want to make him jealous, but it creeps in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you spend your Sundays differently when you started to work, or did you still continue to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 We've always kept it alike, we does to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you begin to take an interest in politics when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No, no more than voting. No further than voting did I ever do anything towards politics at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And you were a Labour man, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, what could I bed. There again, I haven't been in favour with it all. But what am I, to start with? I'm just \{BLANK\} next of kin

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way as you had done when you were at school, or did you start doing different things?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Well, when I left school I naturally got interested with other youths and one were in the brass band world, you see. Well, once you start to learn to play
 an instrument it took a lot of your spare time in learning, and once you got learning and got established into band then, of course, you were out 6 or 7 days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 How old would you be when ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 I were 19, when I started to learn to play. I s
hould've gone in sooner because I'd've done better, but I did all right. But 20 years is a long while in a life. And that took a lot of me time up, and that's helped me to associate in other musical sessions ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1525005\charrsid2688408 \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 pheres, and all. And then even at Church, you understand, the musical side of it, and I made a lot of friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Apart from your band did you go out in the evenings much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 No. No, I've always been an amateur gardener, you see. I've always been an amateur gardener, and I've more gardening n
ow than what I want. I've a few windows that ... 'will you cut me lawn' and one thing and another and I haven't time but I'll do it to oblige, but I've always been interested in amateur gardening ever since I've been at school. I turned me first allotment
 over at 14, before I were 14. In 1914 War turned my first allotment over and we've gardened ever since. That ... I've never done now of me own, no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1525005\charrsid2688408 decorating, no no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 t like that, it's all been spent in me garden, banding, and Church life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you make any new friends round about the time you started to work? Either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
No, because we always fell back onto us old associates, even at school life. You see, what you learnt at school and village community, you still retained it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have any special friends about that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I think you've all nearest and dearest, haven't you, you see, nearer than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you spend much time with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, yes, throughout us late 'teens and courtship and even in marriage we'v
e gone on holidays with 'em. And still do it. I've been up to Scotland 6 year with another couple, this last 6 year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 When you were a teenager you had girlfriends as well as boy friends, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Yes, but my boy friends were always occupationally
, like, in band and gardening, you see. Banding played a big part, you'd plenty of friends in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And what about girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, I were never a ladies man. This is the only association I've had in my life. I mean to say, we went to school togeth
er as children, we lived next}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1525005\charrsid2688408  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 door but one all us life and we're here together, we've been married 40 year this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Oh, as often as were necessary yes. We could always take 'em home, and we always went to them. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And did your parents expect to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 
Oh, by Jove, aye, that were first question that cropped up. 'Where've you been?' But of course, the village community isn't like town and city community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Did you have to be home by a certain time after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 More or less you could say so, yes. If you weren't, they wanted to know where you had been, let's put it that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 And what sort of a time would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 Well, if it were after 10 o'clock they'd want to know, even up to getting married. They would, honestly. And more so with my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2641324 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 You mean her parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629693 GT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14098181\charrsid2688408 With her parents, they'd want to know. But them days and today is different. I mean, life doesn't start today 'ti
ll 10 o'clock at night, does it. We are of that school, are we. That's difference between what you're asking me and what's happening today.
\par }}